latestPosts.caption:
This wasn’t just about running 13.1 miles. It was about showing up for myself every single day. For 3 months, I trained not just my body, but my mind. This journey pulled me out of some really hard days and reminded me of how strong I am. Crossing that finish line meant everything and let me tell you, it was epic. 

What a time to be alive and run alongside 15,000 strong women (& a few men, lol). It was something I’ll never forget. Like the billboard says “Done. But far from finished.” It’s only the beginning… and I’ve never felt more proud. 🫶🏼🥹

Thank you to everyone who sent good luck messages, checked in, and motivated me along the way your support meant more than you know. Next up, I’m hitting that 1/2 marathon under 2 hours.🏃🏼‍♀️🩷
